-- Osaka Proposes Establishing Consumer-Lending Zone With Relaxed Rules
-- Adam Le
-- 2010-07-06T05:11:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/osaka-proposes-establishing-consumer-lending-zone-with-relaxed-rules.html

          
          
             Osaka, Japan’s third-biggest
prefecture, proposed setting up a consumer-lending zone with
looser rules, including a maximum interest rate of 29.2 percent.
Osaka’s prefectural government made the proposal in a statement
issued today at a local press club.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Adam Le in Osaka at 
 ale14@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        